<div class="block-contributor">
		

		<div class="block-contributor-content">
		<div class="block-contributor-bio small">
			<p><strong><span class="smallcaps">Sparrow </span></strong>wonders whether he should sell copies of <em>Born Too Young</em>, his book being excerpted in <strong>The Sun</strong>, &ldquo;for the cost of xeroxing, plus postage. Or, maybe I should rent it to people, for like five dollars. But can I <em>trust</em> people enough to rent them the manuscript? Gee, I don&rsquo;t know. If they don&rsquo;t return it fast enough, should I send them letters of guilt? Get my mother to write them?&rdquo; For more information, write Sparrow, 322 East 11th Street, #23, New York, NY 10003.</p><a href="/contributors/sparrow" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
	</div>
</div>

